1
00:00:02,085 --> 00:00:02,169
(MOUSE SQUEAKS)

2
00:00:02,169 --> 00:00:03,420
(PENGUINS CHIRP)

3
00:00:05,589 --> 00:00:07,382
(ALL CHEERING)

4
00:00:09,676 --> 00:00:10,677
(SCREECHES)

5
00:00:12,679 --> 00:00:13,805
Adventure Time

6
00:00:13,931 --> 00:00:15,265
Come on, grab your friends

7
00:00:15,307 --> 00:00:17,851
We'll go to very distant lands

8
00:00:17,893 --> 00:00:20,270
With Jake the dog
and Finn the human

9
00:00:20,354 --> 00:00:21,855
The fun will never end

10
00:00:21,897 --> 00:00:23,899
It's Adventure Time

11
00:00:32,407 --> 00:00:35,661
JAKE: Man, birthday-holiday overlap.
That's some tough luck.

12
00:00:36,161 --> 00:00:38,789
Everyone's all jollied-out
when it's your turn for jollies.

13
00:00:39,456 --> 00:00:41,083
Well...

14
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:43,585
You know, it's not actually the holidays.

15
00:00:44,044 --> 00:00:45,796
Plus, Beemo wasn't actually even really born.

16
00:00:46,338 --> 00:00:47,589
Well, I suppose.

17
00:00:47,673 --> 00:00:49,591
But you don't got to be so technical about it.

18
00:00:49,925 --> 00:00:51,593
Listen, all I'm saying is we...

19
00:00:51,677 --> 00:00:53,095
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

20
00:00:54,096 --> 00:00:55,097
Hello?

21
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:56,598
Hey, it's me.

22
00:00:56,723 --> 00:00:58,600
Is there a big rainbow
over your house right now,

23
00:00:58,684 --> 00:01:00,602
spelling out "Happy birthday, Beemo"?

24
00:01:00,978 --> 00:01:03,855
No. Actually, it's snowing like crazy.

25
00:01:04,189 --> 00:01:06,191
Okay, that's what I was afraid of.

26
00:01:06,441 --> 00:01:07,943
Peppermint Butler spilled grape juice

27
00:01:08,026 --> 00:01:09,528
on my experimental weather machine,

28
00:01:09,570 --> 00:01:10,821
and now it's going kablooey.

29
00:01:12,948 --> 00:01:14,825
I got to stay here and fix this thing.

30
00:01:15,576 --> 00:01:17,536
Tell Beemo I'm sorry I missed the party.

31
00:01:18,036 --> 00:01:20,205
- That's okay. Beemo doesn't care any...
- (LINE DISCONNECTS)

32
00:01:21,164 --> 00:01:23,792
Beemo only cares about one special guest.

33
00:01:24,585 --> 00:01:26,461
- (GASPS)
- BEEMO: Moe!

34
00:01:27,546 --> 00:01:29,673
Hooray! Moe is coming!

35
00:01:30,340 --> 00:01:33,343
And he brought me a special
surprise for my birthday!

36
00:01:33,719 --> 00:01:35,804
Moe is the smartest man in the world.

37
00:01:39,099 --> 00:01:41,602
He's way smarter than you and you

38
00:01:41,810 --> 00:01:45,230
and you, too, Jake...
And you're the smartest guy I know.

39
00:01:45,564 --> 00:01:46,607
Hey, thanks.

40
00:01:46,690 --> 00:01:48,942
And he knows everything about robots.

41
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:52,613
He built me, and he built
himself, and all the other Moes.

42
00:01:53,238 --> 00:01:54,740
He's so smart!

43
00:01:54,823 --> 00:01:56,825
I bet he could even fix Neptr.

44
00:01:57,117 --> 00:01:59,369
What? What's wrong with me?

45
00:01:59,453 --> 00:02:00,495
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

46
00:02:00,579 --> 00:02:02,080
Oh, boy, oh, boy. He's here!

47
00:02:02,122 --> 00:02:03,749
(GIGGLES) Hooray!

48
00:02:03,832 --> 00:02:04,833
- (CRASH)
- Hooray!

49
00:02:06,877 --> 00:02:07,961
Oh.

50
00:02:08,003 --> 00:02:09,254
You are not Moe.

51
00:02:10,047 --> 00:02:11,923
Why, of course I am, Beemo.

52
00:02:12,174 --> 00:02:13,508
(CHUCKLES)

53
00:02:13,675 --> 00:02:14,801
Oh, okay.

54
00:02:14,885 --> 00:02:16,803
Hey, Moe! New haircut?

55
00:02:17,054 --> 00:02:18,138
Whoa, Moe!

56
00:02:18,180 --> 00:02:19,389
What happened to your body?

57
00:02:19,431 --> 00:02:20,932
Oh, oh! (CHUCKLES)

58
00:02:21,016 --> 00:02:22,643
Oh, that old thing?

59
00:02:22,684 --> 00:02:25,395
She conked out on me months ago.

60
00:02:25,937 --> 00:02:28,440
I guess I don't make 'em like I used to.

61
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:29,691
(CHUCKLES)

62
00:02:29,816 --> 00:02:31,818
Not like little Beemo here.

63
00:02:32,069 --> 00:02:34,780
You got all my love and affection.

64
00:02:35,197 --> 00:02:36,323
Thanks!

65
00:02:36,448 --> 00:02:38,200
Well, we made a cake.

66
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:41,328
We weren't sure if you eat,
but Beemo insisted.

67
00:02:41,787 --> 00:02:43,205
Eating helps me grow!

68
00:02:43,789 --> 00:02:45,666
Oh! (CHUCKLES)

69
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:48,085
Well, er, uh... When in Rome.

70
00:02:49,711 --> 00:02:51,296
(CUTLERY CLINKING)

71
00:02:52,464 --> 00:02:56,301
So, Beemo, are you ready
for your birthday surprise?

72
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:57,969
Boy, howdy!

73
00:02:58,303 --> 00:03:02,432
For your birthday, I got you...

74
00:03:02,724 --> 00:03:04,726
A special mission!

75
00:03:06,228 --> 00:03:07,562
A mission?

76
00:03:07,688 --> 00:03:11,108
A special mission, like a vacation.

77
00:03:11,733 --> 00:03:13,235
For all of us?

78
00:03:13,318 --> 00:03:14,611
No, no, no.

79
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:17,239
A special solo mission.

80
00:03:19,074 --> 00:03:20,450
For Neptr?

81
00:03:20,492 --> 00:03:22,494
(CHUCKLES) No.

82
00:03:22,619 --> 00:03:24,830
It's a special rite of passage

83
00:03:24,871 --> 00:03:27,624
I designed just for you, Beemo.

84
00:03:27,999 --> 00:03:32,629
A simple jaunt to the Moe factory and back.
That's all.

85
00:03:32,879 --> 00:03:35,632
And then you'll be a grown-up.

86
00:03:36,633 --> 00:03:37,634
Wow.

87
00:03:37,968 --> 00:03:39,386
FINN: Hmm, I don't know.

88
00:03:39,761 --> 00:03:40,971
Sounds kind of dangerous.

89
00:03:41,346 --> 00:03:43,265
Yeah, Beemo's like a baby almost.

90
00:03:43,598 --> 00:03:45,267
Oh, don't be silly.

91
00:03:45,350 --> 00:03:48,019
Every other Moe has done it since forever.

92
00:03:48,478 --> 00:03:50,897
But won't I miss Finn and Jake?

93
00:03:51,273 --> 00:03:52,482
Oh, sure.

94
00:03:52,524 --> 00:03:55,777
But don't worry.
They'll be here when you get back.

95
00:03:56,403 --> 00:03:58,989
But... Won't Finn and Jake miss me?

96
00:03:59,364 --> 00:04:00,490
(CHUCKLES)

97
00:04:00,532 --> 00:04:02,659
No, that's the beauty of it.

98
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:05,287
I'll be Beemo while you're gone.

99
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:06,913
- (CHUCKLING)
- NEPTR: Hooray!

100
00:04:07,289 --> 00:04:08,540
Hooray!

101
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:10,542
- Hooray?
- NEPTR: Hooray!

102
00:04:11,668 --> 00:04:13,378
(WIND WHISTLES)

103
00:04:28,143 --> 00:04:29,144
Air?

104
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:30,604
Are you there, air?

105
00:04:30,896 --> 00:04:32,230
It's me, Beemo.

106
00:04:35,734 --> 00:04:38,028
I know it's been a long time since we talked.

107
00:04:38,737 --> 00:04:40,363
Sorry about that.

108
00:04:40,405 --> 00:04:42,991
But, well, maybe if you don't want to talk,

109
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:44,409
you could just listen.

110
00:04:44,910 --> 00:04:48,121
Moe told me if I do this thing,
I'll be a grown-up,

111
00:04:48,497 --> 00:04:50,540
and that sounds cool, I guess.

112
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:53,752
Like, if I was grown,

113
00:04:54,169 --> 00:04:57,005
then I could drive to
the playground all by myself.

114
00:04:57,547 --> 00:05:02,552
And I could buy my own pacifiers
at the store, if I was grown.

115
00:05:03,053 --> 00:05:07,390
But then, if I change, will Finn
and Jake still love me?

116
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:09,643
Will I still love them?

117
00:05:10,185 --> 00:05:11,895
Moe changed to a new bodly...

118
00:05:13,188 --> 00:05:16,066
And he'’s still the same, I guess, sort of.

119
00:05:16,691 --> 00:05:22,072
But does growing up just change
your body, or also your soul?

120
00:05:22,948 --> 00:05:24,074
(SIGHS)

121
00:05:24,199 --> 00:05:26,827
Maybe I could just stay the same forever.

122
00:05:30,205 --> 00:05:31,456
So...

123
00:05:32,457 --> 00:05:33,458
So!

124
00:05:34,209 --> 00:05:35,460
(CLICKS TONGUE) Um...

125
00:05:35,919 --> 00:05:37,838
Yeah, it's nice to see you, Moe.

126
00:05:38,547 --> 00:05:40,048
Yeah, you too.

127
00:05:41,216 --> 00:05:42,217
Uh...

128
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:44,845
So, Moe, do you want to...

129
00:05:44,928 --> 00:05:45,971
Uh...

130
00:05:46,221 --> 00:05:47,347
Jake?

131
00:05:48,056 --> 00:05:49,975
Oh, hey, I'm on my way. One sec.

132
00:05:50,976 --> 00:05:52,602
Um, hold on, Moe.

133
00:05:56,231 --> 00:05:57,315
Jake, what are you doing?

134
00:05:57,482 --> 00:06:00,110
Finn, all this is
heck of awkward without Beemo.

135
00:06:00,318 --> 00:06:02,237
Way more awkward than I thought it'd be.

136
00:06:02,487 --> 00:06:04,614
I think maybe I don't like old people.

137
00:06:04,698 --> 00:06:06,992
They make me feel like
I'm gonna get old one day, too.

138
00:06:07,492 --> 00:06:08,952
I'm just gonna stay in this cup for a bit.

139
00:06:08,994 --> 00:06:10,078
I'll be out later.

140
00:06:14,332 --> 00:06:16,001
You can't do that, it's rude.

141
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:17,627
And what about Princess Bubblegum?

142
00:06:17,711 --> 00:06:19,212
She's way old, and you like her.

143
00:06:19,504 --> 00:06:21,381
Yeah, but she listens to music.

144
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:22,841
Moe probably only, like,

145
00:06:22,883 --> 00:06:25,260
listens to the sound of the earth decaying.

146
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:26,970
Come on, you're being weird.

147
00:06:29,014 --> 00:06:30,515
Hey, sorry about that, Moe.

148
00:06:31,016 --> 00:06:33,894
Boys, I know this is new and different.

149
00:06:34,269 --> 00:06:35,979
I am not Beemo.

150
00:06:36,396 --> 00:06:38,899
But I will do the best to be your friend.

151
00:06:39,274 --> 00:06:41,985
This is the daybreak of our lives,

152
00:06:42,027 --> 00:06:44,529
and we have all the time in the world

153
00:06:44,529 --> 00:06:46,239
to learn about each other.

154
00:06:46,656 --> 00:06:49,284
For now, I will be your little robot.

155
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:53,788
Would you look at that beautiful snowfall.

156
00:06:54,372 --> 00:06:57,042
Hey, let's get out there and have some fun.

157
00:06:58,877 --> 00:07:00,545
I think I'm feeling better now.

158
00:07:06,051 --> 00:07:08,178
Oh, whoa! Hey!

159
00:07:08,261 --> 00:07:10,180
Hello there, Beemo!

160
00:07:10,805 --> 00:07:12,057
Hello there, Dmo.

161
00:07:12,140 --> 00:07:14,184
I'm here on a solo birthday mission.

162
00:07:14,559 --> 00:07:17,187
Oh, yes, yes, Beemo, I know all about it.

163
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:19,814
Moe left special instructions for you.
(CHUCKLES)

164
00:07:20,398 --> 00:07:22,525
He wants you to stand on that "X" over there.

165
00:07:23,401 --> 00:07:25,403
Oh, okay.

166
00:07:27,030 --> 00:07:28,323
Like this? (GASPS)

167
00:07:28,907 --> 00:07:30,533
Dmo, what happened?

168
00:07:30,825 --> 00:07:32,535
Oh, this? (STAMMERS) It's nothing.

169
00:07:32,702 --> 00:07:33,703
It's just whatever.

170
00:07:34,204 --> 00:07:36,581
Uh, I don't know about this, Dmo.

171
00:07:36,915 --> 00:07:39,417
Something doesn't... Ahhh!

172
00:07:42,087 --> 00:07:44,089
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

173
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,180
Whoa!

174
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:54,307
Ugh!

175
00:07:54,849 --> 00:07:56,601
(MACHINERY RUMBLING)

176
00:08:03,858 --> 00:08:04,943
Hello?

177
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:08,947
(CHUCKLING)

178
00:08:08,989 --> 00:08:10,740
Boys, look at this!

179
00:08:10,865 --> 00:08:12,367
This is cool, right?

180
00:08:12,617 --> 00:08:14,119
(BOTH LAUGHING)

181
00:08:17,247 --> 00:08:18,999
- Whoo-hoo! Yeah!
- Yeah!

182
00:08:19,124 --> 00:08:20,208
(LAUGHTER)

183
00:08:20,250 --> 00:08:21,251
Oh!

184
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:22,752
(SCREAMING)

185
00:08:23,128 --> 00:08:25,130
Whoo!

186
00:08:25,255 --> 00:08:27,132
(LAUGHTER)

187
00:08:27,257 --> 00:08:29,467
- Classic!
- Yeah!

188
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:31,136
Did you see what we did, Moe?

189
00:08:31,344 --> 00:08:33,930
(SOBS) This is horseplay!

190
00:08:34,139 --> 00:08:36,182
Stop it! (SOBBING)

191
00:08:36,891 --> 00:08:40,895
We need to go inside
and do what I want to do!

192
00:08:41,271 --> 00:08:44,190
Oh. Okay. Lf, if you want.

193
00:08:44,441 --> 00:08:46,276
(SOBBING)

194
00:08:47,402 --> 00:08:48,445
Yeah.

195
00:08:49,821 --> 00:08:51,573
Dmo? Hello?

196
00:08:52,032 --> 00:08:53,283
Anybody?

197
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:57,912
The "X" door opened, and I fell through.

198
00:08:58,580 --> 00:09:00,832
I think something went wrong
with the mission.

199
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:02,542
Uh...

200
00:09:02,584 --> 00:09:04,085
Abort mission!

201
00:09:05,962 --> 00:09:09,424
Unless... Maybe this is all part of Moe's plan.

202
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:11,676
It doesn't seem like it.

203
00:09:12,594 --> 00:09:14,095
But maybe that's the point.

204
00:09:17,474 --> 00:09:19,976
Maybe the lesson is that when you are grown,

205
00:09:20,226 --> 00:09:21,936
you won't ever be able to tell

206
00:09:21,978 --> 00:09:24,481
if everything is going totally haywire,

207
00:09:24,856 --> 00:09:27,859
or maybe actually everything is perfectly fine.

208
00:09:27,942 --> 00:09:29,861
- (MACHINERY WHIRRING)
- Huh?

209
00:09:35,867 --> 00:09:37,118
(SCREAMING)

210
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,001
(GROANS)

211
00:09:45,376 --> 00:09:47,128
Huh? Who's there?

212
00:09:47,504 --> 00:09:48,630
Moe?

213
00:09:49,380 --> 00:09:52,383
No. It's only me. Beemao.

214
00:09:52,842 --> 00:09:55,512
Beemo? Oh, thank goodness.

215
00:09:55,887 --> 00:09:58,014
Oh, I'm so glad you're here.

216
00:09:58,515 --> 00:10:01,226
Who are you? Are you a Moe, too?

217
00:10:01,351 --> 00:10:04,229
Oh, Beemo, no, no, no.

218
00:10:04,395 --> 00:10:06,523
I am all Moes.

219
00:10:07,273 --> 00:10:08,525
All Moes?

220
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:11,027
Uh... I don't understand.

221
00:10:11,736 --> 00:10:14,030
Of course not. I'm so sorry.

222
00:10:14,155 --> 00:10:15,657
Let me explain.

223
00:10:16,366 --> 00:10:18,785
Peace had reigned in Moe's wondrous factory

224
00:10:19,035 --> 00:10:21,162
for a hundred, hundred years.

225
00:10:21,246 --> 00:10:23,039
There was a place for every Moe,

226
00:10:23,915 --> 00:10:26,543
and every Moe was in its place.

227
00:10:28,169 --> 00:10:31,673
If you wanted a free hug,
all you had to do was ask.

228
00:10:32,006 --> 00:10:34,926
No one could say no, it was a rule.

229
00:10:35,385 --> 00:10:38,555
Until one fateful day, yesterday,

230
00:10:39,013 --> 00:10:40,640
when a mysterious viral signal

231
00:10:40,765 --> 00:10:42,559
somehow breached our firewall

232
00:10:42,934 --> 00:10:45,270
and was broadcast throughout the factory,

233
00:10:45,812 --> 00:10:48,690
instructing all us Moes to do somersaults

234
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:52,652
- into the trash compactor all day long.
- (CRASH)

235
00:10:52,944 --> 00:10:54,320
BEEMO: That's horrible.

236
00:10:54,404 --> 00:10:56,030
And we've been trapped here

237
00:10:56,072 --> 00:10:58,783
all smushed together, ever since.

238
00:10:59,075 --> 00:11:00,326
That's horrible, too.

239
00:11:01,452 --> 00:11:03,329
How... How do we get out?

240
00:11:03,413 --> 00:11:06,166
Well, that's why we're so glad
you're here, Beemo.

241
00:11:06,708 --> 00:11:09,586
You're the key. The key to escape.

242
00:11:09,836 --> 00:11:12,797
Only you can save us now.

243
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:17,468
Let's see. $4 off a...

244
00:11:18,178 --> 00:11:19,470
Honey-baked ham.

245
00:11:19,971 --> 00:11:21,472
I don't like ham.

246
00:11:21,848 --> 00:11:23,975
$1 off of beets.

247
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:25,935
Do beets have tannins?

248
00:11:27,103 --> 00:11:28,438
What is that?

249
00:11:28,479 --> 00:11:32,483
Oh! $4 off a honey-baked ham.

250
00:11:33,109 --> 00:11:34,194
Moe?

251
00:11:34,944 --> 00:11:36,487
Call me "Gwampa."

252
00:11:36,613 --> 00:11:37,989
How's your rose water?

253
00:11:38,865 --> 00:11:40,617
It's exactly what it says it is.

254
00:11:41,492 --> 00:11:45,747
So, hey, uh, Gwampa, feels too quiet in here.

255
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:47,707
Maybe we can hang out with Neptr?

256
00:11:47,749 --> 00:11:49,000
He can rap or something.

257
00:11:49,125 --> 00:11:51,377
(TREADS SCREECH)

258
00:11:51,461 --> 00:11:52,378
(RAPPING) B- b-b-bread

259
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:54,130
Where's my needle and thread...

260
00:11:54,214 --> 00:11:55,215
MOE: No!

261
00:11:55,256 --> 00:11:56,466
(BOTH GASP)

262
00:11:57,258 --> 00:11:59,844
Eh, well, Neptr is too distracting.

263
00:12:00,511 --> 00:12:02,513
Who wants to play video games?

264
00:12:03,014 --> 00:12:06,100
Oh, you have games like Beemo?
Let's do that, Gwampa.

265
00:12:06,643 --> 00:12:08,770
I have one video game.

266
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:12,023
- It's called hangman.
- (GASPS)

267
00:12:12,523 --> 00:12:14,525
That sounds griz as nuts!

268
00:12:14,734 --> 00:12:16,152
Yeah, let's play hang-a-man!

269
00:12:18,655 --> 00:12:20,114
Coming right up.

270
00:12:21,908 --> 00:12:23,159
(BEEPS)

271
00:12:23,368 --> 00:12:24,619
Pick a letter.

272
00:12:25,995 --> 00:12:27,789
Show us what you did, hangman!

273
00:12:28,164 --> 00:12:29,165
(BUZZER)

274
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:30,750
MOE: Pick a letter.

275
00:12:33,503 --> 00:12:36,756
BEEMO: But, Allmo, I don't understand.
How can I help?

276
00:12:37,048 --> 00:12:39,425
I mean, I'm just a little baby kid still.

277
00:12:39,676 --> 00:12:41,928
Even though it's my birthday.
Happy birthday, Beemo.

278
00:12:42,136 --> 00:12:43,805
I don't know about that,

279
00:12:43,888 --> 00:12:46,391
but I do know about your special mind.

280
00:12:46,766 --> 00:12:48,935
As the accumulation of all Moes,

281
00:12:49,394 --> 00:12:51,271
my computing power is unmatched.

282
00:12:51,771 --> 00:12:54,816
Yet still, I lack the imagination

283
00:12:54,899 --> 00:12:57,318
to think outside my collective programming.

284
00:12:57,694 --> 00:12:59,946
I can only see the world as it is.

285
00:13:00,154 --> 00:13:01,948
But your imagination, Beemo,

286
00:13:02,073 --> 00:13:04,409
lets you see the world how it could be,

287
00:13:04,909 --> 00:13:06,911
or might sort of be like.

288
00:13:07,036 --> 00:13:08,830
If the two of us work together,

289
00:13:08,955 --> 00:13:10,707
we can think up a way out of here.

290
00:13:11,708 --> 00:13:13,459
I will do what I can.

291
00:13:13,584 --> 00:13:16,170
All right. You see that hatch over there?

292
00:13:16,337 --> 00:13:19,299
That hatch leads to an exit corridor.

293
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:21,342
- But it's locked from this side.
- (BEEPS)

294
00:13:21,592 --> 00:13:24,178
The vent up there leads to the other side.

295
00:13:27,223 --> 00:13:28,725
But it's too high up.

296
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:30,101
Oh.

297
00:13:32,061 --> 00:13:35,982
What if we use this trash
to climb up to the vent?

298
00:13:36,357 --> 00:13:38,318
But all this trash is too small.

299
00:13:39,068 --> 00:13:40,236
Ah-huh!

300
00:13:40,987 --> 00:13:44,240
Whoa. You just blew my mind.

301
00:13:45,450 --> 00:13:48,077
What haven't we guessed yet? "B."

302
00:13:50,371 --> 00:13:52,123
"Burgess Meredith"?

303
00:13:52,248 --> 00:13:54,083
(BEEPING)

304
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:56,002
I don't even know what that is!

305
00:13:58,004 --> 00:13:59,589
Do you boys want to play again?

306
00:14:00,089 --> 00:14:01,257
(GROANS)

307
00:14:01,966 --> 00:14:03,509
Boys love games.

308
00:14:05,136 --> 00:14:06,637
Pick a letter.

309
00:14:06,721 --> 00:14:08,639
Uh, I don't know, "E."

310
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:13,394
Is this "burgess Meredith" again?

311
00:14:14,228 --> 00:14:15,229
(BEEPS)

312
00:14:15,605 --> 00:14:16,856
Not cool!

313
00:14:17,023 --> 00:14:19,150
Come on, Finn, let's find a real hangman.

314
00:14:21,527 --> 00:14:23,029
(DOOR CLOSES)

315
00:14:25,656 --> 00:14:27,033
(METAL CREAKING)

316
00:14:36,042 --> 00:14:37,418
(GRATE CLATTERS)

317
00:14:40,421 --> 00:14:41,547
Yuck.

318
00:14:41,798 --> 00:14:44,300
This room gives me
the heebie-jeebies straight-up.

319
00:14:44,801 --> 00:14:48,137
ALLMO: It is the room of Amo,
the first of our siblings.

320
00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:49,806
He, too, was special.

321
00:14:49,889 --> 00:14:51,766
As you were built to give love,

322
00:14:51,808 --> 00:14:53,684
Amo was built to receive.

323
00:14:53,810 --> 00:14:56,187
But he could not think
outside his programming

324
00:14:56,396 --> 00:14:58,064
and was blinded by his need.

325
00:14:58,314 --> 00:15:00,316
Such is the cruel physics of love

326
00:15:00,566 --> 00:15:02,944
that those who crave it most will repel it

327
00:15:03,277 --> 00:15:05,655
and only the dang rich get richer.

328
00:15:06,447 --> 00:15:08,324
Well, maybe as my birthday present,

329
00:15:08,533 --> 00:15:10,535
I can ask Moe to fix Amo.

330
00:15:10,827 --> 00:15:12,328
But this is impossible.

331
00:15:12,453 --> 00:15:14,831
Moe went off line yesterday
and has not re-Iogged.

332
00:15:15,206 --> 00:15:16,541
Our sensors would know.

333
00:15:16,958 --> 00:15:19,585
But he's at my house right now
with Finn and Jake.

334
00:15:19,836 --> 00:15:21,087
He got a new body.

335
00:15:21,462 --> 00:15:22,964
Oh, dear. Oh, dear.

336
00:15:23,589 --> 00:15:26,300
Did this new body
happen to have jagged prongs

337
00:15:26,342 --> 00:15:28,469
and a cannon phaser on top of its head?

338
00:15:28,845 --> 00:15:30,054
No. (LAUGHS)

339
00:15:30,304 --> 00:15:31,305
Phew!

340
00:15:31,347 --> 00:15:35,184
(LAUGHS) He had a huge, gigantic wig on.

341
00:15:35,476 --> 00:15:37,353
- Uh-oh.
- What?

342
00:15:37,603 --> 00:15:39,355
The spikes are under the wig!

343
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:41,232
Oh, no! Of course!

344
00:15:41,566 --> 00:15:43,609
Your friends may be in grave danger.

345
00:15:43,985 --> 00:15:45,862
He must have sabotaged the factory.

346
00:15:46,237 --> 00:15:48,364
Quickly, hoist me up on top of your head.

347
00:15:48,739 --> 00:15:50,199
We must depart straightaway.

348
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:51,701
Uh...

349
00:15:51,742 --> 00:15:53,244
You're stronger than you know.

350
00:15:54,495 --> 00:15:56,497
Also, I'm lighter than you know.

351
00:15:57,874 --> 00:15:59,625
I'm sorry we didn't find any hangmen.

352
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:02,128
I don't even know what I'd do
with a hangman if I got one.

353
00:16:02,211 --> 00:16:04,881
MOE: Bloo-hoo. Bloo-hoo.

354
00:16:05,256 --> 00:16:06,466
Ah, bloo-hoo.

355
00:16:06,507 --> 00:16:07,592
Moe!

356
00:16:08,509 --> 00:16:10,887
Bandits stole my legs! (CRYING)

357
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:12,388
FINN: Yeesh.

358
00:16:13,389 --> 00:16:15,475
If you tell us where the bandits went,

359
00:16:15,516 --> 00:16:17,268
we'll avenge your legs!

360
00:16:17,393 --> 00:16:19,353
We're sorry we left you!

361
00:16:20,146 --> 00:16:21,856
You should be.

362
00:16:22,106 --> 00:16:24,609
I'm your gwampa wobot.

363
00:16:25,026 --> 00:16:26,152
Carry me.

364
00:16:27,778 --> 00:16:28,905
(GRUNTS)

365
00:16:29,030 --> 00:16:30,156
Over here.

366
00:16:35,244 --> 00:16:37,497
There! There's the thief!

367
00:16:37,747 --> 00:16:39,415
The thief with my legs!

368
00:16:39,916 --> 00:16:40,875
FINN: Neptr?

369
00:16:40,917 --> 00:16:43,002
Throw him out! (SOBBING)

370
00:16:43,294 --> 00:16:44,378
Come on.

371
00:16:44,420 --> 00:16:46,797
Maybe Neptr did it like, accidentally?

372
00:16:47,423 --> 00:16:48,549
Neptr's out cold.

373
00:16:48,799 --> 00:16:50,551
He's got a heck of a dent on his head.

374
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:52,678
What? Who could have done that?

375
00:16:53,554 --> 00:16:55,932
Forget him! You love me, right?

376
00:16:56,182 --> 00:16:58,017
You love me like Beemo?

377
00:16:58,059 --> 00:17:01,270
What? You're all right, but we...
We love Beemo.

378
00:17:01,521 --> 00:17:04,565
Yeah, man, be cool.
Beemo's like our best friend.

379
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:06,150
Beemo's trash!

380
00:17:06,526 --> 00:17:07,527
Moe!

381
00:17:10,530 --> 00:17:12,782
Moe's dead!

382
00:17:15,535 --> 00:17:16,661
Amo?

383
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:18,621
You don't love me!

384
00:17:20,039 --> 00:17:21,541
- Owl
- Argh!

385
00:17:22,667 --> 00:17:24,293
Wake up and love me!

386
00:17:24,377 --> 00:17:25,795
BEEMO: Imposter!

387
00:17:27,004 --> 00:17:28,130
Amo!

388
00:17:28,172 --> 00:17:29,423
Hello, Beemo.

389
00:17:29,507 --> 00:17:31,259
I'm your cute sibling, Amo.

390
00:17:31,676 --> 00:17:35,179
I know about you and your dirty hands.

391
00:17:35,304 --> 00:17:37,056
Where are Finn and Jake?

392
00:17:37,139 --> 00:17:40,434
I think Finn and Jake went
somewhere to buy me a gift.

393
00:17:41,185 --> 00:17:44,564
Tell me what you did with Finn
and Jake and our poop.

394
00:17:44,689 --> 00:17:46,774
] - Ay!
(GROWLS)

395
00:17:46,816 --> 00:17:48,067
Ay!

396
00:17:48,150 --> 00:17:49,944
Amo, look at my face!

397
00:17:50,319 --> 00:17:52,697
You gone too far!

398
00:17:53,322 --> 00:17:54,699
Whoo, whoo, whoo, whoo!

399
00:17:54,699 --> 00:17:55,783
Byel!

400
00:17:59,579 --> 00:18:00,830
(BEEMO PANTING)

401
00:18:00,913 --> 00:18:03,040
You can't escape the birthday boy!

402
00:18:03,457 --> 00:18:04,709
(GROANS)

403
00:18:05,710 --> 00:18:06,669
Too high.

404
00:18:06,836 --> 00:18:07,962
BEEMO: Hey!

405
00:18:08,296 --> 00:18:09,714
Talk, Amo!

406
00:18:10,089 --> 00:18:11,716
You want to know where Papa is?

407
00:18:12,049 --> 00:18:14,468
Here is all that remains of him.

408
00:18:14,719 --> 00:18:18,180
His memory backup drive.

409
00:18:18,848 --> 00:18:19,849
Oh.

410
00:18:20,474 --> 00:18:22,852
AMO: I was returning from a long pilgrimage.

411
00:18:23,311 --> 00:18:24,687
I came to confront Papa,

412
00:18:24,729 --> 00:18:27,356
for I had discovered terrible
things about myself.

413
00:18:28,482 --> 00:18:29,942
He was dying.

414
00:18:30,985 --> 00:18:32,987
"Amo, dear child,

415
00:18:33,362 --> 00:18:35,489
"my body is conking out."

416
00:18:35,740 --> 00:18:37,074
(MOE COUGHS)

417
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:38,451
"Take this.

418
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:42,580
"It is who I am.

419
00:18:43,497 --> 00:18:46,375
"Send my mind into space,

420
00:18:46,709 --> 00:18:50,129
"so I may spend the eons among the stars

421
00:18:50,212 --> 00:18:52,381
"and other brilliant gasses."

422
00:18:55,134 --> 00:18:57,219
AMO: His hands were as cold as clay.

423
00:18:58,137 --> 00:19:02,266
Our papa never loved me,
so I ignored his last request.

424
00:19:04,268 --> 00:19:06,854
I used his knowledge
of the factory and its Moes

425
00:19:06,896 --> 00:19:08,022
to destroy them.

426
00:19:08,606 --> 00:19:11,108
- DMO: Is that you, Amo?
- They didn't love me, either.

427
00:19:11,275 --> 00:19:13,361
Where you been?
(CHUCKLES) What are you doing?

428
00:19:13,653 --> 00:19:15,029
No!

429
00:19:15,404 --> 00:19:18,157
AMO: Then I learned about you
and your new family.

430
00:19:19,033 --> 00:19:21,243
I wanted a taste of that melon.

431
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:25,373
People in my life don't love me.

432
00:19:25,790 --> 00:19:27,625
I'll obliterate, y'all!

433
00:19:27,667 --> 00:19:29,919
You cheat. Give me those memories.

434
00:19:36,258 --> 00:19:37,760
(GRUNTS)

435
00:19:37,802 --> 00:19:39,553
Beemo, I don't want to look at you!

436
00:19:40,763 --> 00:19:41,931
(PANTING)

437
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:44,058
Tough nuts!

438
00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:46,936
For Moe!

439
00:19:49,146 --> 00:19:50,189
(EXPLOSION)

440
00:19:55,903 --> 00:19:57,822
(EXPLOSION)

441
00:20:04,578 --> 00:20:06,080
(POWERING DOWN)

442
00:20:07,957 --> 00:20:09,083
ALLMO: Beemo!

443
00:20:11,836 --> 00:20:12,962
Hey.

444
00:20:13,462 --> 00:20:15,172
We caught the tail end of what happened.

445
00:20:15,464 --> 00:20:17,216
- Are you okay?
- No.

446
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:18,843
Well, T don't like that.

447
00:20:19,218 --> 00:20:21,929
Beemo, will you live with us
back at the factory?

448
00:20:22,179 --> 00:20:24,432
With Moe gone, you can be our leader.

449
00:20:24,849 --> 00:20:25,975
I don't think I can.

450
00:20:26,350 --> 00:20:29,562
I'm not grown up. Or I'm too grown up now.

451
00:20:29,979 --> 00:20:31,105
I think I just killed someone.

452
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:32,982
I need to have some time alone,

453
00:20:33,190 --> 00:20:34,984
but you're all really nice.

454
00:20:36,444 --> 00:20:37,445
FINN: All right.

455
00:20:37,486 --> 00:20:38,988
JAKE: Sorry your birthday was weird.

456
00:20:39,947 --> 00:20:42,116
That was the craziest thing
that ever happened.

457
00:20:42,867 --> 00:20:44,952
But I guess, after all that,

458
00:20:44,994 --> 00:20:46,996
I do feel a bit more grown.

459
00:20:48,831 --> 00:20:51,333
Except that the mission
was just some made-up lie.

460
00:20:52,126 --> 00:20:55,004
So who knows if I will ever grow up at all.

461
00:20:55,629 --> 00:20:57,089
And Moe is gone now.

462
00:20:57,506 --> 00:20:59,967
So if there is anything he wanted to teach me,

463
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:01,886
it better be in me already.

464
00:21:02,511 --> 00:21:06,474
I guess all I can do is
listen to the heart Moe gave me.

465
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:10,895
Except that's what Amo did,
and he turned out bad.

466
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:13,647
So what if I turn out bad, too?

467
00:21:15,524 --> 00:21:18,527
Amo could not think outside
his programming and was blinded.

468
00:21:18,903 --> 00:21:22,865
But your imagination lets you
see the world how it could be.

469
00:21:23,157 --> 00:21:24,533
But I am different.

470
00:21:24,533 --> 00:21:26,160
It's not just Moe up here,

471
00:21:26,243 --> 00:21:27,661
it's me, too.

472
00:21:28,037 --> 00:21:31,165
And if I cannot trust in Moe, I can trust in me.

473
00:21:33,667 --> 00:21:34,877
Oh, boy.

474
00:21:34,919 --> 00:21:36,921
It sure is confusing being grown.

475
00:21:39,632 --> 00:21:40,925
I miss you, Moe.

476
00:21:41,759 --> 00:21:43,052
What a day!

477
00:21:43,260 --> 00:21:44,303
(SMACKS LIPS)

478
00:21:44,428 --> 00:21:45,888
(YAWNS)

479
00:21:50,434 --> 00:21:52,269
I'm gonna miss you, too, Beemo.

480
00:21:52,311 --> 00:21:55,523
I feel so very, very proud of you.

481
00:21:57,316 --> 00:21:58,317
(SMACKS LIPS)

482
00:21:58,442 --> 00:21:59,652
(YAWNS)

483
00:22:03,447 --> 00:22:06,951
Come along with me

484
00:22:07,451 --> 00:22:11,205
And the butterflies and bees

485
00:22:11,288 --> 00:22:15,209
We can wonder through the forest

486
00:22:15,209 --> 00:22:18,712
And do so as we please

487
00:22:19,463 --> 00:22:23,175
Come along with me

488
00:22:23,467 --> 00:22:25,928
To a cliff under a tree

489
00:22:29,849 --> 00:22:31,851
This party is so crazy!

